  <h>infinitivals</h>
  <p>Infinitivals are a kind of <a href="?xx=nouns/verbal_nouns">verbal noun</a> phrase used with a
    range of different constructions in Gaelic.</p>
  <p>What makes an infinitival different from other verbal noun phrases is that that a direct object
      <emph>precedes</emph> the verbal noun and is in the nominative case, rather than following it
    in the genitive eg. the infinitival <m>an <emph>litir</emph> a leughadh</m>
    <en>reading the letter</en> versus the usual verbal noun phrase <g>leughadh na
        <emph>litreach</emph></g>. </p>
  <p>The infinitival of an <emph>intransitive</emph> verb is formed from the unlenited verbal noun
    followed by its complements and modifiers eg. <ul>
      <li><m>seinn</m>
        <en>singing</en></li>
      <li><m>gabhail ris an tairgse</m>
        <en>accepting the offer</en></li>
      <li><m>smaoineachadh gun robh thu ceart</m>
        <en>thinking that you were right</en></li>
      <li><m>fàgail a-màireach</m>
        <en>leaving tomorrow</en></li>
    </ul>
  </p>
  <p>The infinitival of a transitive verb consists of the object in the nominative, the inverting
    particle <g>a</g>, followed by the lenited verbal noun and other complements and modifiers eg. <ul>
      <li><m>an leabhar a sgrìobhadh</m>
        <en>writing the book</en></li>
      <li><m>òran a gabhail</m>
        <en>performing a song</en></li>
      <li><m>ubhal a thoirt dhomh</m>
        <en>giving me an apple</en></li>
    </ul>
  </p>
  <p>The particle <g>a</g> is usually omitted in both speech and writing if the lenited verbal noun
      <emph>begins</emph> with a vowel sound eg. <ul>
      <li><m>ubhal ithe</m>
        <en>eating an apple</en></li>
      <li><m>an uinneag fhosgladh</m>
        <en>opening the window</en></li>
    </ul>
  </p>
  <p>The particle <g>a</g> is also sometimes omitted if the direct object phrase <emph>ends</emph>
    with a vowel sound eg. <ul>
      <li><m>an duine mharbhadh</m>
        <en>killing the man</en></li>
    </ul>
  </p>
  <p>The intransitive verbs <a href="?gd=bi"><g>bi</g></a> and <a href="?gd=rach"><g>rach</g></a>
    form infinitivals as if they were transitive eg. <ul>
      <li><m>a bhith cinnteach</m>
        <en>being certain</en> and <emph>not</emph>
        <bad>bith cinnteach</bad></li>
      <li><m>a dhol dhachaigh</m>
        <en>going home</en> and <emph>not</emph>
        <bad>dol dhachaigh</bad></li>
    </ul>
  </p>

